item.description:
It is very time-consuming to write up the HEADLINE of your each post. This article is aiming to show you a bash command based way to set up the HEADLINE in the post.
#!/bin/bash ## ~/bin/wa hppath=&quot;~/u2/www/homepage&quot; d=`date &#39;+%Y-%m-%d&#39;` t=`date &#39;+%b %d, %Y %H:%M:%S&#39;` filename=${1// /_} head=&quot;---\n&quot; cd ~/u2/www/homepage/_posts/ postpath=&quot;~/u2/www/homepage/_posts&quot; # touch $d&quot;-&quot;$filename&quot;.md&quot;` echo -e &quot;$head&quot; &gt; &quot;$d&quot;-&quot;$filename&quot;.md vim &quot;$d&quot;-&quot;$filename&quot;.md Add execute permission on this file:
chmod +x ~/bin/wa Usage:
